subject: HISTORY
text: In our earlier History, invasions of this island were easy and frequent. Illustrate and account for this circumstance.

text: Account for the temporary success and the ultimate failure of English policy either in Scotland or in France, in the Middle Ages.

text: Discuss the view that the Great Civil War was rendered inevitable by the character and ambitions of James VI. and I. and Charles I. Trace the steps by which James II. and VII. lost the throne.

text: Select the five greatest names in British History from (1689) to (1832) and, in two instances, give your reasons for your choice.
